OL,3,CCoroner warns of e-bike dangers after
OL,4,Cboy dies in fire
OL,6,FThe blaze, on 4 August, was sparked by
OL,7,Fthe ignition of the bike's lithium
OL,8,Fbattery. Fires involving these
OL,9,Fbatteries, which are also used for e-
OL,10,Fscooters, can spread rapidly and
OL,11,Fproduce a toxic vapour.
OL,13,F13 people died from fires involving e-
OL,14,Fbikes and e-scooters in 2022 and 2023,
OL,15,Faccording to figures published in
OL,16,FAugust by the Office of Product Safety
OL,17,Fand Standards (OPSS).
