OL,3,CCoroner warns of e-bike dangers after
OL,4,Cboy dies in fire
OL,6,FThe area coroner for Liverpool and the
OL,7,FWirral, Anita Bhardwaj, has sent a
OL,8,Fpreventing future deaths report to the
OL,9,FOPSS, the National Fire Chiefs Council
OL,10,Fand Merseyside Fire and Rescue Service
OL,11,Fhighlighting concerns that the public
OL,12,Fneed to be better informed about the
OL,13,Fdangers of storing e-bikes and e-
OL,14,Fscooters at home.
OL,16,FMs Bhardwaj said: "The general public
OL,17,Fdo not appreciate the life-threatening
OL,18,Frisks involved with having lithium
OL,19,Firon batteries, from electronic bikes
OL,20,Fin this case, stored in domestic
OL,21,Fproperties.
