OL,3,CCoroner warns of e-bike dangers after
OL,4,Cboy dies in fire
OL,6,F"There appears to be a lack of
OL,7,Fcommunication/media coverage about the
OL,8,Fdangers involved with storing
OL,9,Fappliances such as electronic bikes/
OL,10,Fscooters in domestic properties.
OL,12,F"There have already been three deaths
OL,13,Fassociated with lithium batteries in
OL,14,Fthe home in Merseyside and we have
OL,15,Fbeen informed there were a number of
OL,16,Fsimilar fatalities across England."
OL,18,FThe coroner believes there is a risk
OL,19,Fthat more deaths could occur unless
OL,20,Faction is taken. Recipients must
OL,21,Frespond by 3 February 2025.
